# The Emergence of Complexity — v2 Design Plan

## Design Brief

Remove ugliness and inconsistency. Give the article a cohesive visual language
that matches its narrative: **a walk from one brick to infinite dimensions**.

Each "step" is a station on a path. The reader moves forward, and each station
has the same rhythm: **Question → Exploration → Consequence**.

---

## Design System

### Typography
- Body: `--font-sans` (JetBrains Mono, the site's global font)
- Math display: `--font-serif` (Georgia) for prominence
- All labels: uppercase, `tracking-[0.2em]`, tiny `[9px-12px]`
- KaTeX everywhere — no raw HTML `<sup>` hacks

### Color Progression (one color per step)

```
Step  | System  | Color Token
──────┼─────────┼─────────────────────
01    | ℕ       | --category-tutorial   (green)
02    | ℤ       | --category-how-to     (purple)
03    | ℚ       | --category-explanation (orange)
04    | log     | --category-data-viz    (blue)
05    | i       | --accent              (rose)
06    | ℂ       | --primary             (teal)
```

Each step's accent color is set as a CSS variable on the section container.
All child diagrams and callouts inherit it — no per-component color hardcoding.

### Animation Primitives (single source of truth)
Defined once in `styles.css`, used by all components:

| Name    | Transform             | Use case              |
|---------|-----------------------|------------------------|
| fade-in | opacity               | static elements        |
| slide-up| translateY(12px)      | staggered text        |
| pop     | scale(0→1) + opacity  | nodes, badges         |
| draw    | stroke-dashoffset     | lines, curves, axes   |
| halo    | scale + opacity pulse | glow effects          |

All durations and delays via CSS custom properties: `--anim-duration`, `--anim-delay`.

### Component Architecture

```
index.mdx          — article content (MDX)
styles.css         — shared animations + component styles
utils.ts           — canvas utilities (HiDPI resize, IntersectionObserver)
Figure.astro       — universal figure card (consistent border/radius/label position)
Callout.astro      — question (?) / consequence (→) — unified, variant prop
StepHeader.astro   — step divider with color accent + progress indicator
Hero.astro         — full-width canvas banner
SvgNode.astro      — reusable SVG <g> node (circle + label + optional subtitle)
TheOne.astro       — "1" brick diagram
TheSuccessor.astro — 1→2→3→4 chain
TheNaturals.astro  — ℕ number line
TheZero.astro      — subtraction fracture
TheIntegers.astro  — symmetric ℤ line
TheDivision.astro  — division shatter
TheRationals.astro — rational density zoom
TheNestedSets.astro— ℕ⊂ℤ⊂ℚ⊂ℝ⊂ℂ overview
TheExponent.astro  — exponential curve
TheLogarithm.astro — eˣ vs ln(x)
TheGrowth.astro    — linear vs logarithmic
TheTransgression.astro — x²+1 parabola with no real root
TheImaginaryUnit.astro  — i rotation cycle
TheComplexPlane.astro   — a+bi vector in 2D
TheRotationCycle.astro  — interactive ×i canvas
TheMasterpiece.astro    — Euler summary table
```

### Layout & Spacing
- Each Step section starts with `StepHeader`, wrapped in a `<section>` with a
  CSS variable `--step-color` on it
- Diagrams: `mx-auto max-w-3xl` (can be wider than prose) or `max-w-sm` for small
- The `Figure.astro` wrapper: ` bg-card border-border rounded-lg border`
- Label badge: `absolute top-3 left-4 font-mono text-[0.6rem] tracking-widest`
- Use `my-12` between steps for clear visual breathing room

### Prose Integration
- Article text stays inside `prose prose-playground` (from site layout)
- Components use `` to opt out of prose styling
- Math: `$...$` inline, `$$...$$` display — KaTeX handles rendering
- Code: inline `` `...` `` in prose for numerals and symbols

