## Narrative Structure (6 Steps + Epilogue)

| Step | Title                      | Question                              | Consequence                              |
|------|----------------------------|---------------------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| 01   | The Natural Numbers        | "What if something exists?"           | From one brick + one rule, infinity      |
| 02   | Zero and Negatives         | "Can we undo an addition?"            | The line becomes symmetric               |
| 03   | The Rationals              | "Can we undo a multiplication?"       | The line becomes dense                   |
| 04   | Logarithms                 | "Given the result, what exponent?"    | Multiplication becomes addition          |
| 05   | The Imaginary Unit         | "What number, squared, gives -1?"     | Pure logical will creates i              |
| 06   | The Complex Plane          | "Where does i go?"                    | Multiplication becomes rotation          |
| —    | Euler's Formula            | —                                     | Five constants converge                  |

